      "problems": "The Docker build process failed multiple times due to installation issues of required packages. Key problems included missing dependencies like 'libssl1.0.0', 'rocksdb', 'ursa', and 'libindy'. Specifically, the build failed at Step 4 with an error indicating missing packages during installation. In Step 6, certificate verification issues prevented fetching necessary files from repositories. The final failure in Step 16 occurred while attempting to install 'python-rocksdb', which indicated a missing header file 'rocksdb/slice.h'. Another recurring issue was the ImportError for 'indy_node.server' during test execution, indicating incomplete or incorrect installation of dependencies.",
      "actions": "The initial approach involved creating a Dockerfile with an Ubuntu 20.04 base image and installing required packages. Attempts to install dependencies were made in a sequential manner, but multiple errors were encountered related to missing packages, incorrect repository sources, and package conflicts. The approach evolved by attempting to adjust the package sources to point to correct repositories and architectures, but most installations failed. Workarounds included removing certain problematic packages from the installation list, but these often led to missing dependencies needed for the project.",
      "progress": "50% complete. The Docker image has been built successfully in Step 17, but subsequent attempts to run tests failed due to missing modules and dependencies. The installation of critical packages like 'python-rocksdb' was unsuccessful. The environment is partially set up, but the test suite preparation is incomplete and blocked by missing modules.",
      "lessons": "The project requires specific versions of dependencies, including 'python3-nacl', 'libgflags-dev', and 'python-rocksdb'. Configuration issues arose from outdated or incorrect repository sources. The project's testing setup relies on pytest, and specific modules like 'indy_node.server' must be correctly installed to run tests. It was noted that certain packages may not be available in the specified repositories for Ubuntu 20.04, necessitating more careful selection of base images and package versions.",
      "suggestions": "1. Modify the Dockerfile to ensure all required repositories are correctly listed and accessible. 2. Try using a different base image that is known to work with the project's dependencies, or consider using Ubuntu 22.04. 3. Remove 'libssl1.0.0', 'rocksdb', 'ursa', and 'libindy' from the installation list in the Dockerfile and check if the environment builds successfully. 4. When running tests, ensure that all required modules are installed by verifying the installation with: pip show <module_name>. 5. Use 'pip install -r requirements.txt' to ensure that all dependencies are satisfied before executing tests.",
      "dockerfile_recommendation": "FROM ubuntu:22.04\n\nARG DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive\nENV TZ=Europe/Berlin\n\nRUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y git gnupg wget apt-transport-https ca-certificates curl jq python3 python3-pip python3-nacl python3-dev g++ libgflags-dev libsnappy-dev zlib1g-dev libbz2-dev liblz4-dev zstd ruby ruby-dev rubygems gcc make\n\nWORKDIR /app\n\nARG REPO_URL=https://github.com/hyperledger-indy/indy-node\nRUN git clone --depth 1 \"$REPO_URL\" indy_node\n\nWORKDIR /app/indy_node\n\nRUN pip install .[tests]\n\nCMD [\"bash\"]",
      "dockerfile_used": "FROM ubuntu:20.04\n\nARG DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive\nENV TZ=Europe/Berlin\n\n# Install git separately first\nRUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y git\n\n# Install gnupg before adding keys\nRUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y gnupg\n\n# Add additional repository signing keys\nRUN apt-key adv --keyserver keyserver.ubuntu.com --recv-keys 9692C00E657DDE61 && \\\n    apt-key adv --keyserver keyserver.ubuntu.com --recv-keys CE7709D068DB5E88\n\n# Clean up required apt sources without duplicates\nRUN echo \"deb http://ports.ubuntu.com/ubuntu-ports focal main universe\" > /etc/apt/sources.list && \\\n    echo \"deb http://ports.ubuntu.com/ubuntu-ports focal-updates main universe\" >> /etc/apt/sources.list\n\n# Install system dependencies including g++\nRUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \\\n    wget apt-transport-https ca-certificates apt-utils curl jq \\\n    python3 python3-pip python3-nacl python3-dev g++ \\\n    libgflags-dev libsnappy-dev zlib1g-dev libbz2-dev liblz4-dev \\\n    zstd ruby ruby-dev rubygems gcc make librocksdb-dev\n\nRUN pip3 install -U \\\n    setuptools==50.3.2 \\\n    'pyzmq==22.3.0' \\\n    Cython==0.29.36\n\n# Setup project directory\nWORKDIR /app\n\n# Clone the repository\nARG REPO_URL=https://github.com/hyperledger-indy/indy-node\nRUN git clone --depth 1 \"$REPO_URL\" indy_node\n\n# Change to the project directory\nWORKDIR /app/indy_node\n\n# Install the project and its test dependencies\nRUN pip --cache-dir /root/.cache/pip install .[tests]\n\n# Clean up apt cache\nRUN apt-get -y autoremove && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*\n\n# Command to run tests\nCMD [\"bash\"]"
